{"word":"χήρα","slug":"χήρα","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b><el>χήρα, ας, ἡ</el></b> [<a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ cp.\">cp.</a> <el><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:χῶρος\">χῶρος</a></el> ‘empty’, of a space or place] ‘a woman bereft of her spouse’, <b>widow<p class=\"pp3\"/>—<pp>a.</pp> <a href='B:470 23:13'>Mt 23:13</a> [14] <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ v.l.\">v.l.</a>; <a href='B:480 12:40'>Mk 12:40</a>, <a href='B:480 12:42'>42f</a>; <a href='B:490 2:37'>Lk 2:37</a>; <a href='B:490 7:12'>7:12</a>; <a href='B:490 18:3'>18:3</a>, <a href='B:490 18:5'>5</a>; <a href='B:490 20:47'>20:47</a>; <a href='B:490 21:2'>21:2f</a>; <a href='B:510 9:39'>Ac 9:39</a>; <a href='B:530 7:8'>1 Cor 7:8</a>; <a href='B:610 5:3'>1 Ti 5:3a</a>, 4, 11, 16.</b> In the bombastic denial of the apocalyptic prostitute <b><a href='B:730 18:7'>Rv 18:7</a>.<p class=\"pp3\"/>—<pp>b.</pp></b> of widows receiving special consideration <b><a href='B:610 5:3'>1 Ti 5:3b</a>, 9.</b> <center id=\"nav_bottom\"> <a id=\"left_arrow\" href=\"S:Χεροῦβ\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> <a id=\"bottom_home\" href=\"S:#1.Table of Contents\">&emsp;&emsp;</a> <a id=\"right_arrow\" href=\"S:χιϚʹ\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> </center> "}]}